entry.tran: (鞋或靴尖起保护或加固作用的)外包头
entry.def: A toecap is a piece of leather or metal which is fitted over the end of a shoe or boot in order to protect or strengthen it.

means.word_mean: 1. leather covering the toe of a boot or shoe and reinforcing or decorating it
